PorchKeep — credits & third-party software

- eufy-security-ws  https://github.com/bropat/eufy-security-ws  (MIT-licensed)
  Wrapper around eufy-security-client that exposes the eufy P2P protocol over
  a local WebSocket. PorchKeep bundles this verbatim into its Resources/ and
  spawns it as a child process at runtime.

- ffmpeg  https://ffmpeg.org/  (LGPL/GPL)
  Used unmodified to mux H.264 elementary streams into .mp4 and to remux to
  HLS for live view. PorchKeep bundles a static ffmpeg binary copied from
  Homebrew's distribution.

- Node.js  https://nodejs.org/  (MIT-style)
  Required to run eufy-security-ws. PorchKeep bundles the host's node binary.

This app is for personal use. It is ad-hoc-signed and not distributed through
the App Store.
